SetHoldings()5/5

            Void QuantConnect.Algorithm.QCAlgorithm.SetHoldings (
    Symbol             symbol,
    Decimal            percentage,
    *Boolean           liquidateExistingHoldings,
    *String            tag,
    *IOrderProperties  orderProperties
   )

Automatically place a market order which will set the holdings to between 100% or -100% of *PORTFOLIO VALUE*. E.g. SetHoldings("AAPL", 0.1); SetHoldings("IBM", -0.2); -> Sets portfolio as long 10% APPL and short 20% IBM E.g. SetHoldings("AAPL", 2); -> Sets apple to 2x leveraged with all our cash. If the market is closed, place a market on open order.

Parameters
Symbol symbol Symbol indexer.
Decimal percentage decimal fraction of portfolio to set stock.
*Boolean liquidateExistingHoldings (Optional) bool flag to clean all existing holdings before setting new faction.
*String tag (Optional) Tag the order with a short string.
*IOrderProperties orderProperties (Optional) The order properties to use. Defaults to DefaultOrderProperties.

Return

Void - This method provides no return.
